inn1.comm: length delivery moves in from outside leg, towards middle, pushed to silly cover region for a quick single
in the zone outside off stump and Smith goes for his cut but failed to connect.
And again! Extra bounce on this one as well. Smith went way under the ball
tries to jab this to the on side and it rolls off the pad
gets forward to defend this quietly to the off side
More leg byes! there were so many in the second ODI. This one bounds off the pad to the fine-leg boundary

Trapped! First ball for Hafeez! What a start. Overcast conditions, supposed to help seam, and what does he do? Strikes first ball with his off break! It drifted in from round the stumps, landed just outside the off stump and moved in with the arm. Again, yet again, Smith pushes well outside the line rather clulessly
this one turns a bit outside off, Bravo eases it to covers
turns from the off stump, pushed out to the off side
leans forward to tap this to the on side
gets back this time and works it to short midwicket
on the pads, turned to backward square-leg fielder
comes in from just outside off stump, defended to the off side
stays back to punch this short-of-length delivery to the off side
short in length, just outside off stump, steered to backward point. He needs to pitch it up a bit and see if this track aids some seam movement
fuller this time, around off, Bravo waits, opens the bat-face and steers it to third man
shuffles across ,gets behind the line of full-length delivery angling across and pushes it to the off side of the pitch
And again. This time he steers the ball to covers.
gets behind the line to defend this to the on side
drags this short and Bravo jumps at it: he went back and cut it through point. The fielder rushes and slides forward and ends up pushing the ball back on to his body! And the ball goes past the ropes
leans forward to defend this to the off side
on the off stump line, guided to point region with the turn
ooh! Lovely off break! Much fun! It drifted in from round the stumps, landed around middle stump and spun sharply, past the edge,  and the keeper coudln't take it cleanly. Extra bounce as well
gets back to defend this to the on side
around the off stump line, tapped in front of him
this one kicks up from short of length and Bravo allows it to pass through to the keeper
stays behind the line of the short of length delivery and pushes it towards covers
stays back to turn this to the square-leg fielder. And he then takes a walk to the on side
around that off stump line, turned to point region.
Nice shot! It was slightly short in length just outside off and Bravo pressed back to punch it neatly through extra cover.
moves outside leg and waits for Hafeez to release the ball. he then steers the ball to point
leans forward to push this quietly to the off side
Again that technique: he moved outside leg before release. He pushed this ball to covers
leans forward to ease this towards long-on for a single
gets forward to nudge this to the leg side
slower, tossed up full, driven down to long-on
short in length, clipped to deep backward square-leg
What a wallop! Stylish and stunning! He moved down the track and whip-flicked it up and over midwicket boundary! Very very nicely done. Wristy
gets forward to defend to short cover region
moves forward to steer this full-length delivery to point
leans forward to wrist this full delivery on leg and middle through midwicket
tries to whip this to the on side but doesn't make contact and the ball rolls off the thigh pad
on the pads, turned towards square-leg for a single
slip and leg slip watch Simmons push this full delivery to mid-off
beaten! He tried that technique of moving outside leg stump. Hafeez pushed this outside off and got it to go on straight and Simmons was beaten on the cut shot
moves down the track for the big hit, doesn't quite reach the pitch of the ball and ends up slicing it up and over point
Crashed! He leaned forward and blasted this full delivery over wide mid-off region
plays the sweep shot this time but finds Shehzad at backward square-leg
Wow! Stunning. It was a full-length delivery just outside off and Bravo glided forward to punch it sweetly up and over wide mid-off region.
gets back this time but punches straight to covers
leans forward to caress a square  drive. Nicely done but the heavy outfield meant it didn't go to the boundary. He moved forward, opened the bat-face and steered it through point
gets back to clip this back-of-length delivery past square-leg
gets back to push this length delivery to covers
on the middle stump line, Bravo gets behind the line to defend it in front of him
around the off stump line, cuts it to covers
turns away from the off, cut to point
quicker one, striaghtish, steered to short third man
cuts this to covers but again straight to the fielder
drives this to long-off where Ajmal fumbles to give away an extra run!
lifts this towards the right of Ajmal, who doesn't make any mistake this time and Afridi, who wasn't pleased last ball, applauds this time
slips down the leg side .. did it brush the pad en route to the keeper?
leans forward to drive this to mid-off. No ball though.
goes for a big slog over midwicket but top-edges it to Shehzad at deep mid-on. Shehzad back pedals to take that "catch" and throws it back
Crunched! It was short of length and there was some width on it and Bravo didn't cut but punched it over extra cover in some style
leans forward to dab this to covers
fuller, finally, and there is hint of movement but its on the leg and middle line and the ball rolls off the pad
length delivery just outside off, punched through extra cover for a single
from round the stumps,  and he screams out an appeal for lbw. It was on the leg stump line and moved past the attemped sweep and rolled off the pad
on the off stump line, tapped down to long-on
from over the stumps, quickish slider but down the leg side, Simmons tries to clip it but is struck on the pad, outside leg
Whoa! 80.1 MPH quick seam-up delivery from Afridi! It was on the middle stump line, from a length, defended
gets forward to drag this slower one over to wide long-on region
tries that approach of moving outside leg to the spinners. And tastes success this time. He cut this short of length delivery to the point boundary
gets forward to defend this to the on side
fullish delivery around off and middle, driven to mid-off.
short in length outside off, punched away to sweeper cover
Slugged! he cleared the front foot, waited and swung the full-length delivery around off to wide long-off region. He carved that
Ah! Wahab offers a short ball on the leg side and Simmons plays a stylish pull to the fine-leg boundary
in the zone outside off, run down to third man for a single
turning away from Simmons who cuts but its intercepted at covers
drifts to the pads, moves past the prod and rolls off the pad
on the middle stump line, skidding on, Simmons leans forward to defend that slightly quicker delivery
slower, lands on the leg and middle line and turns, eased to the off side
slower, on a length and outside off, Simmons chases the width but was beaten by the change of pace..
gets back to cut but againt can't beat the off-side field
on a length, on the middle, nudged to the leg side
steers this to backward point
fullish delivery, Bravo edges his off drive to his boot and the ball rolls towards mid-off
stays back to tap this to short midwicket region
just outside the off stump, run down to third man
on the legs, turned to deep backward square-leg
on the middle, Simmons gets the bat around the front pad to turn it to squarwe-leg
leans forward to dab this to point for a single
fuller delivery, on driven to long-on
slips this down the leg side, Bravo tries to sweep but misses
leans forward to nudge this to the off side
nudges it to square-leg for a single
gets forward to defend to covers
gets forward to dab this to the off side
turns from outside leg, worked to the on side
spin and bounce! It turned past the defensive prod and Salman was in trouble! He tried to take it but it climbed almost shoulder high!
lands outside leg, turns, Bravo leans forward to defend the off break
more turn this time but from short of length and that allows Bravo to tap it to right of the diving backward point fielder
full delivery, on the middle, jabbed to midwicket
leans forward to nudge this to the off isde
on the pads, worked to square-leg. No run
beaten! it was in the zone outside off, skidding off quickly, Bravo is beaten on the prod and Salman collects neatly
fuller, outside off, steered to backward point region
presses back to force this through to sweeper cover
Thunderous slog sweep! He went down on the knee and swung the length delivery over midwicket boundary!
gets back to tap this to the off side
around the off stump line, tapped to off sie
low full toss, drifting in, pushed down to long-on
lands full outside off and turns away, left alone
turn and bounce! it landed just outside leg, gripped and spun sharply. And bounced. Bravo does well not to push out at it and the keeper collects
gets well back to cut to backward point
stays back to crucnh this past the diving backward point fielder. This was shorter and probably a touch wider, Simmons cuts it into the gaps.
leans forward to nudge it to midwicket region
50 up flicked away to deep midwicket. Very fine knock so far. The team-mates applaud in the dressing room. full of intent. Good to watch
turning in from round the stumps, jabbed to the on side
plays the sweep to rotate the strike
lands outside leg stump, nudged to front of square-leg for a single
turns away from Bravo who cuts to deep backward point
Simmons went down the track and he perhaps got too close to it. He ended up jabbing and scoooping a return catch. Ajmal lunged to his left to hold on!
gets forward to stab this to the off side. He didn't look comfortable there
drifts from round the stumps, full and on the pads, run down to fine-leg
leans forward to drive to left of the bowler who makes a half-stop. The ball goes to extra cover .
leans well forward to defend this
presses back to turn this to midwicket
backs away a touch to cut through to deep point region
on the off stump line, Samuels stabs it to the off
spins away towards off, punched to backward point
lands outside leg, worked to midwicket
turns away from the off stump, short in length, cut to sweeper cover

Ha! It landed around leg and middle and Samuels leaned forward to defend. What if it was the doosra? And so he carefully sniffed over the ball and found out that it was the off break that was turning down. Samuels removes the bat from the line and the ball hits the pad
gets forwad to carefully negotiate this one
works this through to deep cover point region for a single
gets forward to push it back to the bowler
fuller, outside off and Samuels leans forward to play a nice-looking square drive. He stretched forward to caress it through off
presses right back to punch this to long-on
gets back, makes room and cuts to sweeper cover
turns in sharply, Samuels pushes it off the back foot to covers
gets back to ease this gently through point for a single
full and straight, driven back the bowler, who threatens to throw it back but holds on
the slower off cutter, punched out to deep point region
stays back to tap this length delivery to the off side of the pitch
full in length around off, punched out to long-on and they jog through for a single
full and straight again, wicket to wicket as they say, pushed back to the bowler
around the off stump line, pushed out to mid-off
from round the stumps, lands on leg and middle and turns, defended to the on side
around that off stump, guided to backward point
tries to flick this leg-stunmp line delivery but edges it to his pad
on the middle stump line and Bravo pings long-on
on the middle stump line, tilting in, pushed down to long-on
on the off and middle line, from a length, Bravo backs away, creates room and cuts to sweeper cover
Bravo is awake allright! He thrust his front foot forward and absolutely killed this over long-off. An almost flat-batted whack. Hit on the up
just outside off stump, pushed out to point
slower off cutter, from the leg stump line, nudged to the off
full and outside off, driven on a bent knee but straight to short extra cover
slower one, tapped to the on side
gets back to punch this to deep cover
driven down to long off, the bowler could stop the ball despite a dive

gone! Breakthrough for Pakistan and another West Indies batsman fails to convert a useful start. Bravo played a cross a full delivery and that was heading onto leg stump. The umpire took his time, but made the right decision
this takes the pad through short fine-leg
worked out to square leg
onto the back foot and flicks out to deep square-leg
defended into the off side
outside off and left alone...fairly tight and it also bounced a lot to the keeper
forced off the back foot into the covers
beauty! Spin and bounce completely beats Samuels...terrific delivery from Afridi
and now he's nearly through him with a googly that hurries through but Samuels is able to find the gap out to deep cover
drifts onto leg stump and tucked away into the leg side
on the back foot and can't find a gap in the leg side
on off stump, stays on the back foot and defends
worked into the square leg area
is clearly trying to play Ajmal off the pitch and turns this backward of square
beaten by a very full one, almost a yorker, which he plays over the top of...doesn't have much idea here
lunges onto the front foot and blocks
finally gets it away as he tucks it off his hip down to fine leg...tight over from Ajmal
just outside off, cut away to point
on the middle stump line, skidding in, agian cut straight to point
slower, width outside off, Samuels reaches out but mistimes the cut to covers
presses right back to defend to the on side
flighted full on the middle, pushed back to the bowler
nice one, slower, fuller and teasing width outside off, sliced off the edge to backward point
from round the stumps, length delivery on the middle, pushed out to square-leg
from round the stumps, on the middle and leg, pushed gently to the on side
fullish, around the off stump line, tapped to the off
full and straight, outside off, eased to left of cover fielder for a single
slower, full and around that off and middle line, driven to Ajmal at long-off
fullish, on the legs, turned down to fine-leg
around the off stump line, pushed out to point
tuk-tuk cricket continues as the batsman taps it ever so gently to the off
and pushes this to backward point. No intent
leans forward to drive to the off-side field
And this time straight to covers. Maiden over.
Almost caught! Samuels mistimed the forcing shot and edged it over point and Umar Akmal rushed back and dived forward but coudln't reach it
stays back and steers this to backward point
width on offer, cut to deep point. Just a single, though
swing and a miss. He went for an hoick but the ball flew past the bat and over the middle stump

Junaid picks his first wicket! Little big moment for him! It was a length delivery that shaped in off the seam, from round the stumps. Samuels was in no position to play a forcing shot - he was on the back foot and tried to force this through off and only managed to get a fatal inside edge
Edges it to third man boundary! he tried to drive this on the up through off and edged it to left of third man who made a fumbling tumbling effort
full and well outside off, driven to sweeper cover
stays back to tap this to point region for a single
length delivery angling across, punched out to sweeper cover
gets forward and across to push to cover point
just outside off, guided straight to backward point
stays at the crease and punches this wide of sweeper cover for couple of runs
tossed up full, driven down to long-on
leans forward to push it back to the bowler
Heave-master! It was tossed up full outside and Kirk, who has been stonewalling so far, dragged it high to the left of long-on where Junaid rushes and jumps but it goes over him
quickish off break on middle and off, tapped to the off side
the doosra! on the middle and off line, nudged off the back foot
another doosra, this is on the middle and leg line, swatted down to fine-leg

Kirk is run out. It jagged up towards the rib cage and Bravo hopped to stab it.. The ball rolled towards backward point. Bravo didn't want a run but Kirk Edwards was charging across. Umar Akmal swooped in, picked the ball, and fired a direct hit at the non-striker's end. Clatter!
around the off stump, steered to point
delivered from close to the stumps, bounces around off, guided to third man
the bouncer and it flies over Sammy, who went down to get away from the line of fire
short in length outside off, punched through to sweeper cover
full and well outside off, Bravo goes for the lofted cover drive but doesn't reach it.
glides across to knock this through to sweeper cover
from round the stumps, on the leg side, run down to fine-leg .. Was there any bat involved? Thought it went off the thigh
leans well forward to defend this back down the track
lands around middle, goes away towards off, Sammy drags it around to deep midwicket region. it was slightly short
this one is fuller and it skids away from the off stump, delivered from round the stumps, Bravo doesn't connect with the cut
quicker, around off, full, Bravo hurries back to defend
leans forward to tap this to silly mid-off region and for some strange reason he wants a single. No, thank you , says Sammy
on the pads, swung away in that wristy free-style of Sammy to fine-leg region
full and angling across Bravo who edges the intended big off drive to third man

Why not take the batting Powerplay if you going to slog like this? IT was a short delivery outside off and he slogged across- flat batted it - high to left of long-on where Shehzad pouches it. Sammy shakes his head as he walks off.
in the zone outside off, from back of a length, Bravo tries to steer it to backward point and is beaten!

Another one ! What is happening out there? Poor  thinking. It was a short-of-length delivery outside off and Bravo tried to knife through the line but could't handle the extra bounce. The ball wobbled away to long-on. Batting Powerplay is yet to be taken
Almost another wicket! From round the stumps this time, Wahab bangs in a bouncer, and the batsman is late on the pull. The ball lobs in the air but falls wide of midwicket
ooh! the doosra from round the stumps and it skids past the nervous poke
tosses this up, full on the leg stump line, swept away to fine-leg. Ajmal smiles.
slip and silly point watch Russell shoulder arms to this quicker delivery outside off
tries to sweep this slower one but this is the doosra and it rolls away of the pad to slip
full and on the middle, dabbed to midwicket
tries the reverse sweep but the ball lands just outside leg and almost takes out the leg stump!
from round the stumps on the middle, nurdled to midwicket
full and outside off, Roach tries to square drive but no wood on leather

shuffles across to push it to backward point. Almost a run out there. Russel had charged across, Umar picked the ball a nd fired the throw but missed the stumps a t the non striker's end. Wahab was in the way and he got out. Wonder whether Wahab's presence affected Umar.
taps this the leg side. West Indies tottering here on 161 for 7
still from round the stumps, in the zone outside off, just about holding its line and Roach is beaten, pushing inside the line

They continue to tumble here. Roach is troubled by this round-the-stumps angle. He tries to work it to the on side, thinking i t will come in with the angle but it doesn't come in as much as he thought. He gets a leading edge on this length delivery and it lobs gently to point
gets well  back to defend this to the off side
flighted full on the middle, tapped to covers
this one breaks back in from off stump line, doosra from round the stumps, Rampaul jabs it to the on side
edges the sweep shot but will pick up a single
ooh la la! What a doosra.. It landed just outside leg, from round the stumps, and broke away sharply past the defensive prod. Salman wasn't fooled though

Quick work from Salman! The batsman rushed down the track, looking for glory. This was the off break and it turned in, went through the bat and pad and ended up outside leg. Salman picked it, moved quickly to his left, collected it and broke the stumps in a flash
full and straight, pushed to the off side
the inswinging full toss, the attempted yorker, squeezed out to on side
the bouncer this time and Salman collects
shortish delivery, chopped  through to left of Salman who dived but the ball bounced before him and jagged away from him.
gets forward to drive to covers
slower one well outside off, swing and a miss. Wide signalled.
pushed towards mid-on for a single
flicks this to midwicket  and by the time the fielder moves in from the deep, they take two
full and on the off, defended to the off side
flighted full outside off, eased through covers
And its over. The end of misery for some West Indies fans. More agony for some. Bishoo tries a reverse sweep and top edges it to backward point!

inn2.comm: Two slips watch Roach spray this wide outside off.
Beauty! it was full, it was pacy and it just about held its line; or rather didn't come in as much as Hafeez thought it would. He pushed inside the line and the ball rushed past the edge
covers the off stump and shoulders arms
Spray! Way down the leg side, perhaps going for more pace and also trying to bring this one back in after those previous away deliveries. Simmons had no chance in getting that back
One-handed square drive! He leaned forward and across for the drive; didn't quite lean into it and so, took the bottom-hand off the handle and went through with the top hand
lets this one zip through to the keeper
fullish, closer to the off and driven to covers

Caught by Simmons! It was banged in short and he went for the big pull shot. He tried to fetch it from outside off and that, coupled with the bounce, did him in. The ball flew up and Simmons went back and waited for the ball to come back to him.

Two in two! Hold on,Windies are having a small phase of joy here. This one landed short of length and held its line. Asad Shafiq hung his bat out to dry and the ball flew low to the right of second slip where Sammy pouches it with skill and glee
lands on a length and moves in towards middle and off, Misbah stayed back to defend
straightens outside off, bounces, Misbah stays back to defend to the off side
fuller in length, misbah stays back to push it back down the track
Misbah leans forward and across to steer this through point for couple of runs.
leans forward to defend to the off side
short in length and a touch wide outside off, steered down to wide third man
in the zone outside off, left alone
kicks up from short of length outside off, steered to point
another one that climbs steeply, Misbah arches back, rides the bounce and pushes it down to the off
in the corridor, left alone

Pakistan have been jolted hard by Ravi Rampaul. He is bouncing them out. "Absolutely crazy batting," says Rameez Raja on air. This was another bouncer - well not quite a bouncer but banged in short of length around that off stump - and Haffez went for the pull. The top edge takes the ball towards square-leg where Bishoo takes it with utmost delight
short in length, around off, tapped to the on side
The short-pitched delivery arrives and Misbah is ready and rides the bounce nicely to defend
leans forward to defend the length delivery to the off side
stays back to turn the back of length delivery to backward square-leg
another one that kicks up outside off, Misbah plays it really well, arches back to steer it down to third man

lifter outside off . Misbah could have perhaps left this one but he does a Rahul dravid. Hops up, raises his hands up, tries to desperately get top of the bounce and pats the ball  back down in front of him

ooh! similar delivery, short and flying outside off, Misbah goes for a very loose flashy shot and the ball flies past the edge. It wasn't the horizontal cut- it needed one if at all he wanted to play an aggressive shot -  but it was a rather risky punchy shot
two slips and gully watch misbah defend this short of length ball to the off

dug in short of length, tapped to point region for a quick single. Bishoo swooped in from backward point and had a shy at the non-striker's end. Misbah just about got back in time. The throw missed the stumps
Just clear of the lunging backward point! It was short of length delivery, bouncing chest-high outside off and Umar stood on his toes and flashed it uppishly to left of backward point
punches this to point region for a single
full n length, on the middle, tapped wide of midwicket for a single
on a length around middle and leg line, clipped through backward square-leg
on the middle line, tapped to short midwicket

edged past second slip. Ravi Rampaul holds his head. It was a full-length delivery outside off and Umar, who has been getting shortish deliveries, tried to lash out at the fuller length. mistake. The ball held its line and flew off th edge but went to the right of second slip
gets across to punch this very sweetly through point and Dwayne Bravo charges after it and pulls of a neat diving sliding stop
on the middle and leg, Umar shuffles across, and unfurls the leg glance to collect another boundary. Neatly done.
length delivery outside off, guided to backward point region

Run out of Misbah missed It was tapped towards say very short midwicket. Roach rushed across, got to the ball, turned and fired the throw at the non-striker's end. Misbah was not even in the frame but the ball bounced past the stumps!
Wild swing and a miss! It was shortish delivery but well outside off, Umar went for a huge pull shot and missed it
gets back to defend this short-of-length delivery to the off
fuller in length, moving in towards middle and off line, Umar nudges it quietly to the on side and gets across
retreats into the crease to defend this to the off. Roach wipes off the sweat from his forehead, collects his hat from the keeper, and has a look at his captain as he walks off
gets back and across to defend this to the on side
drifts to the pads, clipped down to fine-leg region
full in length and misbah reads it correctly and gets forward to defend
shorter in length, misbah stays at his crease and wrists it wide of Bishoo at backward square-leg
Top crunchy shot! It was a short of length delivery outside off and Umar stood on his toes to punch it through extra cover
hops to get on top of the bounce of the short-of-length delivery and tucks it to Bishoo at square-leg
shortish delivery just outside off and Misbah steers it to point
in the channel outside off stump and Misbah lets it fly through to Simmons
fuller, much fuler, Misbah is late to pick up the length and hence late in getting forward; he ends up mistiming the drive to the off side
kicks up from short of length, at the body, tucked through backward square-leg region
the bouncer and this time Umar tries his best to ride the bounce, gets his hands high, gets the bat in front of his face and pushes the ball down
shuffles across, tries to get on top of the bounce and work it to the on side. He succeeded in getting over the bounce but this one straightened and he ended up edging it to the off side
Not all that short this time and Misbah goes for the pull but ends up dragging it to backward square-leg fielder
shortish outside off, Misbah stays side on and steers it to third man
length delivery outside off and Umar is caught at the crease; and he ends up stabbing this to covers
edged to third man. It was a length delivery that held its line around off and middle, and Umar played inside the line
around that off stump line, pushed out to the off
around the off, Misbah taps it to mid-off
well outside off, Umar goes for the forcing shot through off but it was wide and he could only manage to edge it to the off
Connection! This time he went across, got close to the line of short of length delivery well outside off and cut it hard through cover point.
Much better from Russell: Full in length and  more importantly, a lot straighter. Umar defends.
overpitched outside off, driven to right of short extra cover where Samuels makes a diving stop
steered down to third man for a single
tries to cut this one hard but ends up mistiming it to point.
Good short delivery and Umar drags it to right of diving backward square-leg fielder
fuller but sprays it just down the leg side and Umar glances it. It doesn't quite go as well as he would have liked and he ended up clipping it not far from the diving Simmons
on the middle stump line, pushed back to the bowler. Umar puts his right hand up as he shuffles to the leg as if to suggest, Hold on mate, don't throw the ball back at me

What a sharp lovely lifting snorter! Rampaul has taken out Umar Akmal with a beauty. It screamed up at Umar who hopped but jumped right into more trouble. he would have been better off trying to leave it but it's easier said than done of course. He jumped to try get on top of the bounce but it kept climbing. Trouble. He tried to sway away at the last instant. Too late. The ball clipped the edge and flew to the keeper.
full delivery but on the pads, Hammad tickles it past square-leg
around the off stump line, pushed back to the bowler
moves in from outside off and Hammad pats it to the off side
length delivery just outside off, eased out to covers
moves in from just outside off, Hammad gets back to defend it to the off side
moves in towards the pads, worked wide of midwicket for a single
in the zone outside off, left alone
sprays this down the leg side for a wide
in the zone outside off, wobbly seam there, left alone
tries the bouncer but pushes it around the leg stump line, pulled away for a single
full in length, on the middle, Misbah defends and the ball runs to the on side. They rush across for the single
stays back to defend a length delivery to point
presses back to push this carefully to the off side.
Hammad holds tight all right. At least this ball. He gets back to tap it gently to the off
fuller and Hammad stays back but manages to push this one to the off side. Ravi Rampaul gives him an inquistive look
clipped through square-leg for a single
in the channel outside off; for a moment it appeared as if Hammad was thinking about offering a shot but he shouldered arms at the last instant
gets across the stumps and punches it to covers. he didn't quite find the timing there
Stylish pull. Almost calypso. It wasn't all that short and he lifted his front leg in the air and pulled it to deep square-leg.
full in length, misbah gets behind the line to defend. He then suggests he should have got his head over the ball and really killed it right in front of him.
just outside off stump, steered to left of backward point
full in length around off, pushed out to mid-off region
leans forward to drive the full delivery back to the bowler. Will he slip in a bouncer at some point?
on the hips, lapped around the corner for a single
goes for the pull, mises and is hit on the thigh pad. Rampaul winces. It wasn't all that short and it was slightly strange to see Misbah go for the pull shot against that delivery.
gets back to push this to the off side
full in length and in the zone outside off, left alone

Another injudicious pull from Misbah. This was the bouncer and he fetched it from just outside off and went for the pull. He squirted it of  edge to the fine-leg boundary. Not totally in control. Russell holds his head in agony
gets behind the line this time and defends
on the off stump line, tapped close on the off side, both think about the single but decide against it.
over steps the mark and Hammad drives to left of mid-on where a half-stop is made

Tonked! Hammad cleared the front and was about to set himself for the big swing over midwicket when he picked the slower one. He waited and then smashed it way high over midwicket boundary on the roof! New balls please! he clubbed that one. violence!
short and wide from Russell, cut through point region
works this through the on side for a single
gets forward to carefully tap this one away for a single
gets behind the line to defend this
in the zone outside off, left alone
leans forward to drive it to mid-on
attempts the bouncer - tennis-ball bounce there!- and it loops over Hammad, who ducked
fullish, just outside off, Hammad shuffles across to on drive to mid-on
on the middle stump line, this time hammad doesn't shuffle across, holds his position and taps it to the on side of the pitch
That loopy tennis ball bounce again. This one climbs over the batsman.
edged to third man! It was ful in length and outside off. Hammad lunged across to cover drive and edged it for a single
leans well forward to defend this to the off
drops this short and Hammad drags it to right of mid-on for a single
gets back to punch this to extra cover
turns from the middle and off line, pushed back to Bishoo
lands on middle, skids to middle and leg, clipped to square-leg for a single
slows up the pace, still short though and Hammad swats it past square-leg
short in length outside off, pushed out to backward point
full and on the middle stump line, flicked through to deep midwicket for a single.
slower one, just outside off, tapped to point for a single
wide outside off, Misbah reaches out to cut but finds backward point
leans forward to dead-bat this length delivery to the off
full and just outside off, pats this to the off
ooh sharp turn! Hammad leaned forward to defend and ended up chasing this big leg break. Simmons collected
steers this with the turn to backward point
stretches forward, bat and pad close together, to defend
presses back to tap this leg break towards covers
slower, tossed up, fuller, and Hammad paddles it around the corner
leans forward to defend this to covers
shuffles right across and Bravo pushes this to to the leg and middle stump line and it drifts just past the leg stump
Whack! Very good pull. It was short in length and Hammad was quick to jump at it. He swivelled off the front foot and pulled it over square-leg
Ah! Bravo comes back with a good yorker and Hammad digs it out just in time.
lunges forward to defend this length delivery to covers
shuffles right across the stumps, ends up outside off - he does this now and then - and defends
full in length and outside off, eased to covers
shortish, spins away from the off, misbah reaches out to cut it to covers

Jaffa! What a cracking leg break. It drifted in towards middle and leg and Misbah leaned forward to defend. It gripped and spun right across the defensive push and Simmons couldn' t take it. it flew between the keeper and slip.
leans forward to defend to the off side
stretches forward to defend
moves outside leg and waits. It's a shortish ball, and he cuts it away to deep point
drops this slightly short as well, pulled straight to short midwicket
leans forward to defend the full-length delivery to the off
shapes to off drive on the up but mistimes it to mid-off.
just short of length, tapped down to third man
leans forward to defend to covers
around that off stump line, defended on the front foot
driven to left of Bravo who dives full stretch to try stop it but can't reach.
edges the sweep to right of short fine-leg fielder and Misbah calls him over for a quick single. Hammad just about manages to get there
lunges forward to defend and edges it but short of the lunging slip fielder
Shout for lbw but was that  mssing leg stump? It landed on the leg stump line and just about straightened. Hawk eye suggests it had straightened enough to hit the leg stump
Clubbed! Misbah roars back with a thumping six over long-on. He didn't leave his crease but just leaned forward and smoked this high over long-on
Crashed! Too short from Bishoo and Misbah waits on the back foot and smashes it to wide long-on boundary
fuller delivery this time and Misbah leans forward to defend
walks down the track, gets towards off in the process and whips a full delivery through to deep midwicket
fullish outside off, pushed to left of mid-off for a single
in the channel outside off, left alone
short in length outside off, pushed out to point

full in length, on the middle, on driven to long-on. Actually he plays the on drive like a straight drive. He sort of shuffles across, gets almost outside the line, twists his body and drives with a straight bat .. ie from outside off to mid-on
misbah pings long-on this time
full and straight, on driven to long-on
leans forward to defend this to the off
full and straight, eased towards his partner
skids on towards middle from short of length, Hammad forces it down to wide long-on
on the middle and leg, clipped past midwicket
reaches forward to guide this to right of backward point
slips this full and outside leg for a wide
pushes this well outside off, cut away to sweeper cover
slower one, fuller, pushed back to Bravo
on the middle stump line, full in length, Misbah leans forward and wrists it past square-leg and runs hard to push for the second
full and outside off, sliced away to backward point
slower one, fullish, whipped to midwicket and they go for the quick risky single. Bishoo with throw but Hammad was too quick for him

cuts in from around off, Hammad lunges across to defend but had pushed too far across. The ball cut back in to clip the edge and bounded off the thigh. It popped up in front and Bravo started to gets excited and rushed down the pitch but the ball died on him way too early
full in length, on the middle, pushed down to mid-on
short in length, on the middle and leg, turned past square-leg
gets forward to push it to the on side
leans across to defend to the off side
just outside off, dabbed to backward point

the bouncer arrives and Hammad pulls it down to deep square-leg. It was nice to see him get that pull down on to the ground. There was a fielder in the deep and he ensured he pulled the ball to the ground.
full in length, on the off and middle, defended to short midwicket
full in lenght and just outside off, pushed back to the bowler
leans forward to squeeze out the slower one to covers
on the off stump line, punched down to long-on
presses back to punch this to covers
gets forward to drive to left of mid-off for a single
slip and silly point watch Misbah drag this short delivery - Bishoo has bowled quite a few short ones today - from outside off to long-on

Given out lbw though there was an inside edge. It landed full on a length around middle and began to turn towards middle and off. Hammad leaned forward to defend and pushed outside the line. The ball clipped the inside edge and hit the pad. Ump Ashoka thought it must have hit the pad first. Hammad's promising knock is over now. Enter Shahid Afridi.
nice legbreak on the middle and off line, defended to the off side
lovely legbreak! It turned sharply from the leg and middle line and Afridi was beaten, trying to dab it to the off
drops this slightly short, cut away to sweeper cover
Aah! what a shot. He went down on his knee and played a reverse sweep. It wasn't full and so he had to adjust, raise his hands high and swat it to deep backward point boundary

Edged wide of lone slip. It reared up sharply around off stump line and Afridi was in a tangle. He was squared-up and just about stabbed the lifter from around his right shoulder and it flew of the edge
reaches his 50 with a push to mid-on. Afridi gets across to congratulate and Misbah pats him on the back
Slap! It was the short ball around off, he reached forward and slapped it through wide midwicket.
cuts in, moves past the defensive prod and strikes him around the waist
leans forward to jab this to covers
full delivery outside off, square driven to point
Nicely done. This wasn't a slog. He moved outside leg and lifted it, from outside leg, with the turn and over extra cover
Well .. er ... this was a slog. He fetched this leg break from well outside off and went for a big slog. Even as it went in the air towards covers, he looked at his partner and winced.
leans forward to push this to cover point
Very  injudcious sweep shot attempted first ball. And it rolls off the pad. It was turning away from the off stump.
this one spins across Salman who just about holds his bat inside the line

Edged just short of the lunging second slip fielder. Another flighted tempting leg break and Salman leans forward to defend. it dips on him and turns. The edge takes the ball just short of the diving Samuels
short in length outside off, pushed out to point region
in the zone outside off, squirted down to third man
in the zone outside off, chopped down to backward point
short and wide, Misbah goes for the cut but doesn't connect
just outside the off stump, steered to backward point
cuts in towards off, dabbed away to backward point. Salman will be on strike against Bishoo
ooh sharp leg break, turning away from the middle. Salman jabs it off his glove to the off side. No silly point. They have two slips and short leg. Now Sammy moves in a silly point.

Salman takes some risk, fetches this leg break from outside off and drags it through midwicket. He doesn't run the first run! Oh! He was just walking, thinking it will reach the boundary. Poor Misbah was tearing across. Only two runs

If only he had run properly last ball, he wouldn't have been on strike this delivery to face this absolute gem! The deadly flipper! It landed on a length, or perhaps back of a length,  around the off stump line and Salman thought, ok let me cut. Fatal mistake. The ball skidded on quickly and straight towards the off stump before he could get the bat down. Whoosh! Clatter!
lunges forward to defend and it goes off the pad first. Pad, bat and then off the ground to silly point. It was the front-of-the-hand slider
lunges forward to stab this to the off

Wicked legbreak! Shout for lbw It spun too much though. It darted away sharply  from the leg stump line and also bounced. Wahab had no clue as he lunged out and was hit on the back thigh.  It would have missed off stump
taps the first ball for a single. Five to go for Wahab.
short in length around off, tapped to backward point

The West Indies players appeal for lbw and the umpire signals a wide. Replays agree with the umpire. It was close to the gloves - the batsman was trying to glance it- but don't think there was any edge.
Second wide in a row. This one is way outside off. Bravo is losing the plot here
cuts in from just outside off, defended to the off side
drifts to the pads this time, clipped away for a single.
just outside off stump, run down to third man for a single
full and homing in on the off stump, pushed out towards mid-on

on the middle stump line, punched out towards long-on. They complete one and they rush back for the second, Misbah retains strike. He really hared down the track, looked at his partner and turned back
tosses this up, keeps it fuller, leans forward to defend
shortish, outside off, cut away to point.
pushes this quicker. Misbah leans forward to turn it to the on side
slows up the pace on this one, tosses it up around leg, Misbah waits, leans forward and gently taps it to the off

Swept uppishly just clear of backward square-leg fielder. Sammy leaps in agony at point and lands on his knee. Misbah taps Bishoo on the shoulder after reaching the other end. Great scenes here! this was swept aerially past the diving Kirk Edwards and runs away to the boundary. misbah reaches the other end and pats (congratulatory tap) Bishoo!
dug in short, towards the rib cage, tucked to short square-leg fielder. There is a man short on the leg side. a short square-leg or a deep short-leg
a bouncer from round the stumps this time ,, tapped close on the off side, say towards backward point and they rush across. Bravo yelps in agony in that run being taken. Wahab off the strike.
Misbah picks the slower one and eases it through extra cover for couple of runs
this one lands around off and cuts in towards middle. misbah seemed frozen till the last instant. The ball cuts in, moves towards middle when he stirs and chops it away.
slower one outside off, misbah mistimes a drive to mid-off. He then suggests he should have punched it through extra cover.
fullish outside off, misbah drives but the cover fielder intervenes. He will be off strike. Pakistan need ten, Windies need three wickets.
lands on a length around off, straightens a touch, Wahab crouches as he leans forward to defend
punches this short of length delivery to point. He then shadow practises that shot again and smiles. misbah has a wrod with him
on the middle stump line, tapped back to the bowler

Thumped! Wahab has turned violent. He took lots of risk to do that. He cleared the front foot, nearly exposed all his three stumps and and heaved this high over long-on. Wonder whether such a risk was needed at this stage.
Luck is with him. He goes for a wild slog across the line this time and edges it in the air. Catch it was the cry but it falls short of the advancing third man
More strange risks! He moves outside leg and has another slog. The edge takes the ball to the off side towards point. Sammy shakes his head as he wipes off some sweat.

Wahab settles the issue with some aggression. It was the expected bouncer from round the stumps and Riaz was ready for this short ball. He swung his bat and the white ball sailed over square-leg. Pakistan have won the series. Afridi enters the arena
